  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Inclusive humanitarian response for older men and women and people with disabilities affected by COVID-19 in South Sudan</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">HAI and HDC are able to influence the wider response through advocacy, campaigns, technical support and communications to ensure older people are considered and included.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Income and social protection are strengthened and older men and women and PwDs are able to cover their basic needs</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Information and advice on COVID-19 is provided to older people and their carers in an inclusive and accessible way</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Older men and women  and people with disabilities are protected, feel safe and have full access to COVID-19 assistance</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The intervention will promote an inclusive humanitarian response and community support through addressing the key needs (Food, WASH and Protection), and amplifying the voices of older persons through strengthening and expanding older persons structures to increase their inclusion in various COVID-19 and humanitarian services in Juba, South Sudan where high numbers of COVID-19 infections have been recorded.</narrative>
  </description>
